Consider an anisotropic independent bond percolation model on the
$d$-dimensional hypercubic lattice, $d\geq 2$, with parameter $p$. We show that
the two point connectivity function $P_{p}(\{(0,\dots,0)\leftrightarrow
(n,0,\dots,0)\})$ is a monotone function in $n$ when the parameter $p$ is close
enough to 0. Analogously, we show that truncated connectivity function
$P_{p}(\{(0,\dots,0)\leftrightarrow (n,0,\dots,0),
(0,\dots,0)\nleftrightarrow\infty\})$ is also a monotone function in $n$ when
$p$ is close to 1.